rComments: The work load is very high, and research-driven. He has high expectations of his students but is extremely clear and fair in his marking. He is available to students for meetings/consultations. This is by far the hardest class I have ever taken. It is also the most rewarding. It might not seem like it, but this man definitly wants you to succeed.

Stedman may be difficult and he expects a lot from his students, but he's also the only prof who has the courage to test us like academics..if you can't wrap your head around it, get out of university
RUN! A very difficult course, and his expectations are evil. Far too heavy of a work load, and he is not kind about it.
